FIG. 9 is a diagrammatical representation of the inductors coupled to a plurality of electrical circuits, in accordance with aspects of the present disclosure.

claim.claim-text:
The method of claim 9, further comprising:
determining whether at least one of the rotational speed of the rotatable shaft is above a threshold speed and the rotor angle of the generator is above a threshold angle;
if so, sending the control signal to the inducting unit for applying the electromagnetic braking force on the rotatable shaft to maintain synchronism between the generator and the power grid.

The method of claim 9, further comprising:
determining whether the voltage in the power grid is a fault voltage;
if so, sending the control signal to the inducting unit for applying the electromagnetic braking force on the rotatable shaft.

The method of claim 9, further comprising:
determining whether the mechanical power produced by the prime mover is above a first threshold power or the electrical power produced by the power generator is below a second threshold power;
if so, sending the control signal to the inducting unit for applying the electromagnetic braking force on the rotatable shaft.

The method of claim 7, further comprising:
determining whether the mechanical power produced by the prime mover is above a first threshold power or the electrical power produced by the power generator is below a second threshold power;
if so, sending the control signal to regulate the generation of the mechanical power for a pre-determined time period.
